<ui:UiBinder xmlns:ui='urn:ui:com.google.gwt.uibinder'
    xmlns:g='urn:import:com.google.gwt.user.client.ui' xmlns:b='urn:import:com.github.gwtbootstrap.client.ui'>
    <g:HTMLPanel>
        <b:PageHeader subtext="Image Icons as background images using css generation">Base Icons</b:PageHeader>
        <b:FluidRow>
            <b:Column size="4">
                <b:Heading size="3">Description</b:Heading>
                <g:HTMLPanel>
                    In GWT, we can bind images as <i>ImageResources</i>. They will be converted as BASE-64 string, which
                    can be added as source in an image-element. With <i>CSS-sprites</i>, they an be used as background-images
                    in css-files. As you can see in the example code, those css-images can be handled easily using the
                    bootstrap IconType-Framework.
                </g:HTMLPanel>
                <g:HTML><p /></g:HTML>
                <b:Heading size="3">Our example icons</b:Heading>
                <g:HTMLPanel ui:field="panel" />
            </b:Column>
            <b:Column size="4">
                <b:Heading size="3">Java Code</b:Heading>
                <b:CodeBlock ui:field="javacode" />
            </b:Column>
            <b:Column size="4">
                <b:Heading size="3">Css Code</b:Heading>
                <b:CodeBlock ui:field="csscode" />
            </b:Column>
        </b:FluidRow>
    </g:HTMLPanel>
</ui:UiBinder>